page.title: 20Landscape
page.content: Travelling from the West to the East we cross{rolling countryside}into a river valley where the villages of Kenninghall and Quidenham have grown up.This area is{wide open fields}with small patches of woodland.To the East is a large area of undrained{Fen,Lakes and a tributary of the River Thet. In early summer fields that have not been sprayed against weeds are ablaze with the red of field{poppies. Over the last fifty years or so there has been a gradual increase in the field size but the area is basically {unspoilt}by urbanisation or development.
